headline: Assessing Intercontinental Exchange After Strong Multi Year Gains and Premium Valuation Metrics
summary: Wondering if Intercontinental Exchange is still a buy at around $162 a share, or if most of the upside has already been priced in? This breakdown will help you decide. The stock has quietly climbed 1.1% over the last week, 6.4% over the last month, and is up 9.3% over the past year, with a standout 65.3% gain over three years and 53.2% over five years, suggesting long term compounding at work. Recent attention has focused on Intercontinental Exchange's expanding role in financial market...
